org.eng.util

Class AbstractListenerManager<LISTENER,DYN_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.util.AbstractListenerManager<LISTENER,DYN_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractAsyncDataProvider, AbstractProcessController

    public abstract class AbstractListenerManager<LISTENER,DYN_DATA,NOTIFY_DATA>
extends Object
    Maintains a list of keyed listeners. Listeners can be added and removed and called. Subclass simply implements callListener(Object, Object, Object) to call the interface-defined LISTENER method, and makes a call to notifyListeners(Object, Object) when the listeners are to be called.
    Author:
    dawood

        public void notifyListeners(DYN_DATA dynamicCallbackData,
